    "updated_at": "2015-02-20T01:29:53Z",
    "body": "I think he's asking how to know where the tray IS (it's not always bottom-right) - I suspect the answer to that is \"you can't\" - certainly it will be a bespoke thing for Windows (normally bottom-right), Linux (normally top) and OSX (always top?)\n\nEven if you assume it is always in the same place (based on the OS) you then need to know how wide/high the screen is for \"for right or bottom-right position)\n\nI can't find any way to detect screen size in \"main.js\" but you can within a browserwindow so you'll need to create a window (set to not show), open it - it's code can then move it to where it should be and then show it (via remote.getCurrentScreen()....) and voila...\n"
